\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The three-stage data-split protocol. In particular, \textit  {T.~guttata}, \textit  {O.~anatinus}, \textit  {A.~mississippiensis} are isolated from training and validation and held out as the mini-benchmark. For stage 1 and stage 2, the inner train/val split is a rotating sequence-level shuffle, using a k-fold structure with $k=5$; this leads to species overlapping during training, but was the chosen design to maximise the performance on stage 1 target. }}{13}{table.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
