\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {12}{\ignorespaces UMAP projection of DNA transposon embeddings coloured by HDBSCAN cluster identity. The top 20 largest clusters are shown in distinct colours; remaining points are shown in light grey. A total of 72 clusters were discovered, revealing substantial substructure within the DNA transposon class beyond the seven annotated superfamilies. Spatially isolated clusters suggest the model has learned sequence groupings that may correspond to novel biological subfamilies or convergently-evolved sequence variants. UMAP axes have no direct biological interpretation.}}{28}{figure.caption.39}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:clustering_umap}{{12}{28}{UMAP projection of DNA transposon embeddings coloured by HDBSCAN cluster identity. The top 20 largest clusters are shown in distinct colours; remaining points are shown in light grey. A total of 72 clusters were discovered, revealing substantial substructure within the DNA transposon class beyond the seven annotated superfamilies. Spatially isolated clusters suggest the model has learned sequence groupings that may correspond to novel biological subfamilies or convergently-evolved sequence variants. UMAP axes have no direct biological interpretation}{figure.caption.39}{}}
